author: A Vox in the Void
description:
"OH YEAH, IMPERATOR!" - A WARHAMMER SONG. 

"Ain't no rouser but a faith rouser..."

As featured in the recent narration:

https://youtu.be/p4SQB5-JuHE?si=tpgLZplRPS1ws8O9

Lyrics by @ArchiveTerra 
Sung by A Vox in the Void
Backing track - neon desert by Coma Svensson


-LYRICS-

"And Brannicus did look ’pon the heretic hordes,
And though they were many, he was unbowed and unbroken,
Even when they blew off his leg with a coward’s bolt,
He smiled, for the Emperor was with him.

FIRST VERSE 

When I was young I had no direction,
Led astray by sin and blasphemy,
But now I ain’t causing no agitation,
Cos Holy Church is my family.

I’m making moves to convert the heathens,
I’m making moves to spread His Truth.
His Word’s my shield against every daemon
That wanna corrupt the souls of youth.

PRECHORUS 

And lo, Brannicus did reach for his severed leg
And the light of Him on Terra did duly shine
Upon the bloody femur, lifted high for all to see,
And, ’fore laying into heretics all ’round di
title: "OH YEAH, IMPERATOR!" - WARHAMMER 40K SONG
